deck: Rocketed from Kamelot to Earth, Etrigan defends Earth-13 and leads the League of Shadows as the Superdemon!
description:
Bound to the preacher's son Jason Blood on Earth-13, a twilight world where technology and magic exist together, Etrigan was rocketed to Earth from the planet Kamelot and defends his earth in the name of Merlin as Superdemon as well as leading the League of Shadows! A rhyming demon like his dimensional counterparts, Jason releases Etrigan and transforms into Superdemon via a rhyming verse.

"First spells the word. Then word's made law. A curse is strung. A sentence passed. Brought low by Grammar at the last. Thereby was demonkind confined. Enchanted in meter. Rapt in Rhyme. In verse and measure. Set in time. Where naming binds all things to shape, divides the Angel from the Ape--yet all that's measured must decay--all bars--all cages--fall away! Come fiery dawn! The Demon's Way! And thus, with time stretched far too thin for further wordy artifice, Instead these clumsy couplets must suffice--Quit! Quit now, The Form of Man! Rise Superdemon! Etrigan!"

- Superdemon transforming in Multiversity #2

Note: Superdemon technically cameoed unnamed in Superman Beyond 1 with the classic Etrigan design and from Earth 17 drawn by Doug Mahnke. The actual Superdemon appeared on a Multiversity: Society of Superheroes variant cover drawn by Frazer Irving but first appeared in the Multiversity Guidebook in comic as designed by Jae Lee and then starred in Multiversity #2 drawn by Ivan Reis. All were written by Grant Morrison
name: Superdemon

deck: Life's a game for young Frodo Johnson.
description:
Nominally parodying the short-lived and by then already defunct 2000 AD spin-off Diceman (the logo is a direct take-off, but that's about all), but mainly sending up Dungeons & Dragons obsessives, young Frodo Johnson sees everything as an adventure game, and turns to his dice to make decisions.

Somewhat in the same vein as another geeky obsessive created by Lew Stringer for Oink!, Specky Hector. A cameo appearance by Rashy Rachel, a supporting character from Pete and his Pimple, establishes the strip as taking place in the same neighbourhood as Stringer's other Oink! strips.
name: Dice Maniac

deck: An Arkham inmate, belived that the ghost of Benjamin Franklin drive him to his crimes.
description:
Bradbury was a small time arsonist, who was belived that the ghost of Benjamin Franklin drive him to his crimes. He was eventually caught and sen to Arkham Asylum.

As Neron's evil spread throughout the world, Bradbury was still imprisoned in Asylum. Playing poker game with other inmates such as Two-Face and Riddler in the mess hall, during a thunder storm, he started to say, that he can do the "same thing" as Benjamin Franklin. When fellow prisoner denied that he could do that, Two-Face proposed to allow his coin to decide. After toss, he informed him that, the indeed "can do that".

When a fight breaks out in the hospital room, Bradbury suddenly makes a dash for the window. He quickly scales the side of the hospital wall and a bolt of lightning strikes Bradbury dead as he is clinging to a weather vane. A moment later, the entire asylum was plunged into darkness due to a short circuit, resulting from the sudden increase of energy.
name: Bradbury

deck: Kryppen the Poisoner is a madman in Arkham Asylum who used to poison all of his victims.
description:
Kryppen the Poisoner is a madman who used to poison all of his victims. He was one of Arkham Asylum inmates, when Neron's evil spread throughout the world. He heard the ethereal voice of the demon and offered him his soul in exchange for power. However, Nero, first ordered him to perform few tasks.

A short time later, after entire asylum is plunged into darkness, Kryppen suddenly head-buttted Jeremiah Arkham in the nose and loudly claimed that he made a pact with the devil, causing a full-scale riot. However, Kryppen was badly beaten by guards, caught with the others and taken to his cell.

Later, he managed to suprise and killed his guards and imperceptibly got into the kitchen. He begins used his knowledge of poisons to whip up a quick cocktail that he uses to taint the hospital's cooking supplies. When it comes time to serve dinner, all of the patients begin falling over with uncontrollable spasms. Arkham himself eats a tainted cookie and falls to the floor of his office.

With all asylum was incapacitated, Kryppen called the Batman. When he arrived, Poisoner told him that he will surrender the cure so long as Batman willingly murders at least one patient. He also revealed that the corrpution of the moral code of Batman, was that the task that Nero ordered him to fulfill. Batman, who refused to play Kryppen rules, caught him and forced him to eat a sample of his own poison. As fear overwhelmed him Kryppen took Batman to the place where it was hidden cure. All patients were given medicine and Kryppen was left terrified of being discovered by the devil, who will punish him for his failure.
name: Kryppen the Poisoner
